For Martha McNabb, it was a catch of a lifetime.

Taking part in 'the world's richest sportfishing tournament', the Mexican angler managed to snag a  525-pound marlin which earned her team $1.2 million.

But despite hitting the jackpot, McNabb didn't win this year's Bisbee's Black and Blue Marlin Tournament in Mexico because her catch wasn't the heaviest.

