'It was a fish of a lifetime and one definitely on my bucket list,' Williams told grindtv.com. 'I love this tournament and I love the people.'

It took two hours for Williams to drag her catch onto the boat, which was delivered to the scale with only 10 minutes remaining in the event.

The tournament has raised more than $600,000 for local charities, and last year more than $200,000 was donated to charity.

The Bisbee's tournament only 
allows marlin weighing 300 pounds or more to be weighed. Smaller marlin 
are supposed to be released, according to petethomasoutdoors.com.

